# WAF & Firewall Manager

## WAF — Layer 7 HTTP filter

Inspects requests → **allow / block / count / CAPTCHA** before your app. Attaches to **CloudFront, ALB, API Gateway, AppSync, Cognito**.

- **Web ACL** = rules + default action; **first match wins** (priority order)

| Rule | Matches |
|---|---|
| **IP set** / **Geo** | IPs, CIDR, country |
| **Rate-based** | IPs over a 5-min threshold |
| **String / regex** | URI, query, headers, body |
| **SQLi / XSS** | attack patterns |

- **Managed Rule Groups** — Core Rule Set, Known Bad Inputs, Bot Control (no hand-writing)

## Firewall Manager — org-wide

- One policy in the mgmt account → **all member accounts** (WAF, Shield Adv, SGs, Network Firewall, DNS Firewall)
- **Enforce a baseline** + **auto-onboard new accounts** on day one
- **Cue:** "apply WAF/Shield across all accounts" → **Firewall Manager**
